Twitter has shared details about its interventions to fight spam and automation which is used to artificially amplify the prominence of Tweets. The platform said keeping Twitter safe and free from spam is a top priority. “One of the most common spam violations we see is the use of multiple accounts and the Twitter developer platform,” said Twitter. “Twitter prohibits any attempt to use automation for the purposes of posting or disseminating spam, and such behaviour may result in enforcement action.” Twitter provided the following guidelines: